1
00:00:00,500 --> 00:00:02,999
(Previously) This is the letter
that someone sent to my mother,

2
00:00:03,000 --> 00:00:04,699
tricking her into coming
down from the village.

3
00:00:04,700 --> 00:00:06,299
Can you find out who did this?

4
00:00:06,300 --> 00:00:08,176
Why are you trying
to dig up the past?

5
00:00:08,200 --> 00:00:10,600
The one who is most
at fault is your father.

6
00:00:16,300 --> 00:00:17,899
This is clearly murder.

7
00:00:17,900 --> 00:00:20,099
We barely have any evidence left to
help us convict the culprit.

8
00:00:20,100 --> 00:00:21,400
But we have that letter.

9
00:00:22,200 --> 00:00:23,400
The Kusuma people.

10
00:00:24,400 --> 00:00:29,400
About your mother, I won't stop searching.
No matter how long it takes, I will find her.

11
00:00:30,200 --> 00:00:33,500
I love you, Dad. And I love Gaysorn too.

12
00:00:33,600 --> 00:00:36,600
Dad, can you please tell me?
What am I supposed to do, Dad?

13
00:00:37,300 --> 00:00:39,300
Dad!

14
00:00:44,800 --> 00:00:45,801
Tell me!

15
00:00:46,443 --> 00:00:48,268
What do I have to do to get your scent?

16
00:00:48,998 --> 00:00:51,499
I told you that you can't!

17
00:00:51,854 --> 00:00:53,574
Stop lying to me!

18
00:00:55,222 --> 00:00:57,854
Tell me! Tell me now!

19
00:00:58,428 --> 00:01:00,174
What is the secret? Tell me!

20
00:01:02,372 --> 00:01:04,414
Anurak? Hey!

21
00:01:07,507 --> 00:01:08,508
Hey!

22
00:01:10,926 --> 00:01:11,927
Hey!

23
00:02:32,200 --> 00:02:36,200
"Flower Boy" (Episode 8)

24
00:02:52,444 --> 00:02:53,445
Dad?

25
00:02:54,966 --> 00:02:55,974
You're fine now.

26
00:02:57,057 --> 00:02:58,534
Doctor said that you're safe now.

27
00:03:06,172 --> 00:03:07,294
What do you want to tell me?

28
00:03:17,204 --> 00:03:18,205
Camera?

29
00:03:19,198 --> 00:03:20,199
Is it camera?

30
00:03:20,773 --> 00:03:21,774
Yes.

31
00:03:22,265 --> 00:03:23,266
What camera?

32
00:03:30,596 --> 00:03:31,597
House?

33
00:03:32,201 --> 00:03:33,202
Our house?

34
00:03:42,780 --> 00:03:45,054
I got the letter when I went to the market.

35
00:03:45,649 --> 00:03:48,614
People passed it along so I didn't know

36
00:03:48,716 --> 00:03:50,214
who the sender was.

37
00:03:51,974 --> 00:03:55,214
The sender must have known
Gaysorn's mom really well.

38
00:03:56,374 --> 00:03:58,914
They knew where she was

39
00:04:00,065 --> 00:04:01,985
and what to do to get
her to leave the moutains.

40
00:04:03,721 --> 00:04:05,454
Who would know the details

41
00:04:05,870 --> 00:04:07,455
unless they worked with Gaysorn's dad?

42
00:04:09,017 --> 00:04:10,374
Scent's dad and uncle.

43
00:04:11,678 --> 00:04:13,414
Scent lured Gaysorn to the city

44
00:04:13,658 --> 00:04:16,054
because he wanted to bring
back Bussaba's scent, didn't he?

45
00:04:21,094 --> 00:04:22,734
If that's the case, then

46
00:04:24,049 --> 00:04:26,094
one of them killed my mom.

47
00:04:27,036 --> 00:04:28,214
Or both of them.

48
00:04:30,289 --> 00:04:31,920
Gaysorn gave Scent the letter.

49
00:04:34,572 --> 00:04:36,454
Gaysorn, you need to call Scent now.

50
00:04:39,468 --> 00:04:40,774
Put him on speaker phone.

51
00:05:04,464 --> 00:05:05,614
He didn't pick up the phone.

52
00:05:06,434 --> 00:05:07,435
What should I do?

53
00:05:08,201 --> 00:05:10,014
The letter is the only
evidence that I have.

54
00:05:19,774 --> 00:05:20,775
He's calling.

55
00:05:28,212 --> 00:05:31,054
I'm sorry, I was busy.

56
00:05:32,388 --> 00:05:33,866
I saw your call, what is it?

57
00:05:35,598 --> 00:05:37,174
I'd like to ask you about the letter.

58
00:05:40,185 --> 00:05:42,414
Did you find out who sent the letter?

59
00:05:47,894 --> 00:05:48,895
Scent?

60
00:05:50,190 --> 00:05:51,191
What is it?

61
00:05:53,081 --> 00:05:54,774
Hey, are you okay?

62
00:05:56,964 --> 00:05:57,965
We need to meet up.

63
00:05:59,161 --> 00:06:00,774
I want to talk to you in person.

64
00:06:02,988 --> 00:06:03,989
Where are you?

65
00:06:08,825 --> 00:06:09,894
I need the letter back.

66
00:06:11,961 --> 00:06:13,064
I kept the letter at home.

67
00:06:14,269 --> 00:06:15,270
How about this?

68
00:06:15,729 --> 00:06:17,174
Can we talk at my place?

69
00:06:17,580 --> 00:06:19,114
Give me two hours,

70
00:06:20,108 --> 00:06:21,668
I need to sort things out about my dad.

71
00:06:43,956 --> 00:06:45,094
What is your plan?

72
00:06:45,598 --> 00:06:47,174
I need to get the letter back first.

73
00:06:47,673 --> 00:06:48,894
Then what?

74
00:06:49,940 --> 00:06:52,854
Should we expose him?
I can call the reporters.

75
00:06:53,341 --> 00:06:54,451
People need to know about

76
00:06:54,976 --> 00:06:57,176
them using people for making perfume.
They're so doomed.

77
00:06:57,350 --> 00:06:58,351
You can't do that.

78
00:06:58,892 --> 00:07:02,174
The outsiders will know
about the Mudan scent.

79
00:07:02,214 --> 00:07:03,254
What are we going to do?

80
00:07:03,396 --> 00:07:05,388
We don't have enough
evidence to go to the police.

81
00:07:05,412 --> 00:07:08,052
Even if we report to the police,
it will end up in news eventually.

82
00:07:14,414 --> 00:07:15,894
It is up to you, Gaysorn.

83
00:07:16,916 --> 00:07:18,254
What do you want?

84
00:07:26,348 --> 00:07:27,349
I know that

85
00:07:28,537 --> 00:07:30,134
I can't put him in jail.

86
00:07:32,582 --> 00:07:34,182
But at least, he needs to own up for it,

87
00:07:35,294 --> 00:07:36,494
that he hurt my mom.

88
00:07:49,332 --> 00:07:50,333
Hello, Scent.

89
00:07:51,353 --> 00:07:52,534
Yeah, I'm inside the house.

90
00:07:54,484 --> 00:07:56,201
Hello, Mr. Sun.

91
00:07:56,462 --> 00:07:59,014
Nobody's home. Can I help you?

92
00:07:59,268 --> 00:08:01,974
Scent asked me to get
something from the house.

93
00:08:06,249 --> 00:08:07,514
Hello, Mr. Scent?

94
00:08:08,956 --> 00:08:10,214
Sure. Got it.

95
00:08:11,361 --> 00:08:12,774
- This way, sir.
- Right.

96
00:08:52,348 --> 00:08:54,817
- Hello, Scent?
- How was it? Did you find it?

97
00:08:55,654 --> 00:08:56,854
Yeah, I got it with me.

98
00:08:57,702 --> 00:09:00,748
Good, you need to deliver
it to the hospital right now.

99
00:09:01,454 --> 00:09:02,455
You got it, pal.

100
00:09:18,678 --> 00:09:20,494
Mr. Ray? Mr. Mekin?

101
00:09:20,894 --> 00:09:22,014
Is Wittaya home?

102
00:09:22,213 --> 00:09:24,054
He hasn't been here yet.

103
00:09:24,734 --> 00:09:26,894
Cool, we're going to wait inside.

104
00:09:29,452 --> 00:09:32,134
Wait! Hey! What do you mean?

105
00:09:32,183 --> 00:09:33,514
Where are you going?

106
00:09:36,334 --> 00:09:37,535
We will wait for him.

107
00:09:38,955 --> 00:09:41,814
I think you better let us wait here nicely.

108
00:10:09,902 --> 00:10:11,574
- Come here!
- Hey! What is this?

109
00:10:13,314 --> 00:10:15,014
Why are you here? Hey!

110
00:10:15,812 --> 00:10:17,414
Why are there so many of you here?

111
00:10:17,796 --> 00:10:19,054
We need to talk.

112
00:10:19,934 --> 00:10:21,114
About my mother.

113
00:10:22,054 --> 00:10:23,414
There is nothing to say.

114
00:10:23,721 --> 00:10:25,254
Get out of my house! Now!

115
00:10:25,722 --> 00:10:26,723
No!

116
00:10:27,374 --> 00:10:28,175
What?

117
00:10:28,260 --> 00:10:29,894
- Let's go.
- Hey!

118
00:10:30,265 --> 00:10:31,266
Hey!

119
00:10:31,774 --> 00:10:32,774
Let me go!

120
00:11:02,625 --> 00:11:04,694
- Hello?
- Mr. Scent!

121
00:11:04,796 --> 00:11:06,654
Someone took Mr. Wittaya.

122
00:11:07,062 --> 00:11:08,572
What? Who took him?

123
00:11:09,036 --> 00:11:11,206
Mr. Ray, Mr. Mekin

124
00:11:11,585 --> 00:11:13,084
and three other people.

125
00:11:13,436 --> 00:11:15,814
But they dressed differently than us.

126
00:11:21,865 --> 00:11:22,866
Gaysorn?

127
00:11:53,633 --> 00:11:55,334
Get out! Come here!

128
00:11:57,636 --> 00:11:58,637
What the hell is this?

129
00:12:01,854 --> 00:12:02,894
What is it?

130
00:12:09,822 --> 00:12:11,214
Where are you taking me?

131
00:12:14,116 --> 00:12:15,117
What the hell is this?

132
00:12:15,934 --> 00:12:17,334
You killed my mom

133
00:12:18,254 --> 00:12:19,495
and buried her here.

134
00:12:41,483 --> 00:12:42,614
I didn't do it.

135
00:12:43,054 --> 00:12:45,055
You can't blame me without any evidence.

136
00:12:45,101 --> 00:12:46,914
- We have the evidence.
- What evidence?

137
00:12:47,051 --> 00:12:50,414
The letter that you wrote to fool Bussaba
to leave the mountains.

138
00:12:51,774 --> 00:12:52,854
The letter?

139
00:13:04,014 --> 00:13:05,015
We need to meet up.

140
00:13:06,316 --> 00:13:07,814
I want to talk to you in person.

141
00:13:10,116 --> 00:13:11,117
Where are you?

142
00:13:14,548 --> 00:13:15,549
I need the letter back.

143
00:13:17,545 --> 00:13:18,654
I kept the letter at home.

144
00:13:19,889 --> 00:13:20,890
How about this?

145
00:13:21,276 --> 00:13:22,654
Can we talk at my place?

146
00:13:23,244 --> 00:13:24,654
Give me two hours,

147
00:13:25,783 --> 00:13:27,343
I need to sort things out about my dad.

148
00:13:27,784 --> 00:13:28,894
The letter?

149
00:13:56,502 --> 00:13:57,503
What letter?

150
00:14:00,017 --> 00:14:01,574
There is no letter.

151
00:14:07,084 --> 00:14:08,214
Where is the letter?

152
00:14:11,714 --> 00:14:14,014
There is no more letter for you.

153
00:14:36,396 --> 00:14:38,174
Mr. Ray? Mr. Mekin?

154
00:14:38,694 --> 00:14:39,934
Is Wittaya home?

155
00:14:40,068 --> 00:14:41,814
He hasn't been here yet.

156
00:14:42,414 --> 00:14:44,614
Cool, we're going to wait inside.

157
00:14:44,990 --> 00:14:45,991
Let's go.

158
00:14:47,225 --> 00:14:49,894
Wait! Hey! What do you mean?

159
00:14:50,102 --> 00:14:51,214
Where are you going?

160
00:14:57,494 --> 00:14:58,495
[The maid]

161
00:14:58,689 --> 00:14:59,854
Why is she calling me?

162
00:15:27,572 --> 00:15:29,894
You don't have any
evidence to incriminate anyone.

163
00:15:30,510 --> 00:15:31,511
You should let me go

164
00:15:32,151 --> 00:15:34,714
or I will press charges
for illegal confinement.

165
00:15:39,278 --> 00:15:41,014
Nobody can own up to this?

166
00:15:46,132 --> 00:15:47,133
What?

167
00:16:03,021 --> 00:16:04,022
Tawan!

168
00:16:05,216 --> 00:16:06,726
Tawan! No!

169
00:16:07,115 --> 00:16:08,120
I will kill him!

170
00:16:08,734 --> 00:16:10,545
He deserves to die after
what he did to Gaysorn's mom.

171
00:16:10,569 --> 00:16:11,570
No! Tawan!

172
00:16:12,206 --> 00:16:14,514
I don't care. I will kill him.

173
00:16:14,538 --> 00:16:17,418
He killed Gaysorn's mom,
how could I let him go?

174
00:16:19,874 --> 00:16:21,614
I didn't kill Bussaba.

175
00:16:22,774 --> 00:16:26,014
The person who killed Bussaba is my brother.

176
00:16:26,454 --> 00:16:27,655
It's Scent's dad.

177
00:16:45,028 --> 00:16:46,029
Where are you going?

178
00:16:46,249 --> 00:16:48,046
Tawan! That's enough!

179
00:16:51,593 --> 00:16:53,214
Was it Scent's dad? Really?

180
00:16:53,908 --> 00:16:54,909
That's right.

181
00:16:56,014 --> 00:16:58,614
His dad was obsessed with making
the perfume and he lost his mind.

182
00:16:59,430 --> 00:17:01,342
He really wanted to come up
with a perfume with your mom's scent.

183
00:17:01,366 --> 00:17:04,134
So he kept her in a room
and tortured her until she died.

184
00:17:05,334 --> 00:17:07,254
He is my own brother

185
00:17:07,750 --> 00:17:09,694
so I needed to bring her dead body

186
00:17:09,772 --> 00:17:11,454
to bury right here.

187
00:17:17,773 --> 00:17:19,174
When I see you all react like this,

188
00:17:20,114 --> 00:17:21,254
I feel bad for you.

189
00:17:21,796 --> 00:17:24,174
And I feel bad for what happened.

190
00:17:25,444 --> 00:17:27,854
But my brother already
paid for what he did.

191
00:17:29,812 --> 00:17:30,813
So what?

192
00:17:32,030 --> 00:17:33,294
You're not satisfied with that?

193
00:17:34,311 --> 00:17:36,812
Are you going to put a
bedridden person in jail?

194
00:17:37,686 --> 00:17:40,214
I'm not going to stop you,
you should do what you want.

195
00:17:47,766 --> 00:17:49,013
Stop lying already.

196
00:17:51,382 --> 00:17:52,383
Scent?

197
00:18:08,382 --> 00:18:09,734
You think nobody would find out

198
00:18:10,329 --> 00:18:13,294
that you were the cause of
what happened to Bussaba?

199
00:18:13,854 --> 00:18:15,254
What did I do?

200
00:18:17,294 --> 00:18:18,295
Gaysorn,

201
00:18:18,974 --> 00:18:21,134
this is the clip that my dad recorded

202
00:18:21,932 --> 00:18:23,254
before he became like this.

203
00:18:30,369 --> 00:18:32,894
I am Anurak Sukontawanich.

204
00:18:34,809 --> 00:18:36,534
I can't take it any longer.

205
00:18:37,534 --> 00:18:39,614
I keep seeing Bussaba in my head

206
00:18:40,854 --> 00:18:42,214
but she was already gone.

207
00:18:44,077 --> 00:18:45,134
She is dead.

208
00:18:47,646 --> 00:18:50,694
It's because of Wittaya,
he accidentally killed her.

209
00:18:57,732 --> 00:19:00,694
Wittaya was obsessed with Bussaba's scent

210
00:19:02,206 --> 00:19:04,934
and he accidentally pushed
Pruek down the stairs.

211
00:19:05,662 --> 00:19:08,054
He also tricked Bussaba
to leave the mountains

212
00:19:10,286 --> 00:19:11,894
so I can start my experiments on her,

213
00:19:12,281 --> 00:19:14,574
hoping to recreate Bussaba's scent.

214
00:19:16,614 --> 00:19:17,914
Wittaya said that

215
00:19:19,105 --> 00:19:21,494
this scent will be our future.

216
00:19:23,036 --> 00:19:24,374
Without the scent,

217
00:19:26,574 --> 00:19:27,734
Bussaba will be done for.

218
00:19:29,758 --> 00:19:31,014
We forced her

219
00:19:31,838 --> 00:19:32,839
until one day

220
00:19:33,555 --> 00:19:35,134
she was dead.

221
00:19:37,614 --> 00:19:38,615
You lied to me.

222
00:19:39,214 --> 00:19:42,294
You blamed it on my dad
when you were the one who killed her!

223
00:19:43,465 --> 00:19:45,134
You killed Gaysorn's parents.

224
00:19:48,814 --> 00:19:50,215
All you got is this clip.

225
00:19:51,337 --> 00:19:53,814
You dad lost his mind back then.

226
00:19:54,201 --> 00:19:55,414
His words can't be trusted.

227
00:19:56,078 --> 00:19:58,254
Your dad killed them, not me.

228
00:19:58,892 --> 00:19:59,892
Sure, if you said so.

229
00:20:00,465 --> 00:20:02,694
I guess you remember
what happened in this clip as well.

230
00:20:12,834 --> 00:20:14,854
Where are you going?

231
00:20:17,977 --> 00:20:19,014
Why are you crying?

232
00:20:19,785 --> 00:20:21,014
Help! Help!

233
00:20:21,780 --> 00:20:24,214
Stop moving! Stop it!

234
00:20:25,614 --> 00:20:27,014
I told you to stay still!

235
00:20:29,862 --> 00:20:31,664
Stay still! Come on!

236
00:20:56,254 --> 00:20:57,255
Wittaya?

237
00:20:58,825 --> 00:20:59,826
She's dead.

238
00:21:19,670 --> 00:21:20,671
Here.

239
00:21:23,334 --> 00:21:24,734
You should do whatever you want to.

240
00:21:25,740 --> 00:21:27,094
I will take care of the rest.

241
00:21:56,361 --> 00:21:58,313
How could you do this to me!? Scent!

242
00:21:59,275 --> 00:22:00,946
How could you do this to your family?

243
00:22:01,371 --> 00:22:02,571
You ungrateful son of a bitch!

244
00:22:06,301 --> 00:22:07,454
I have to, uncle.

245
00:22:08,380 --> 00:22:09,381
I have to.

246
00:22:21,924 --> 00:22:23,294
Mr. Wittaya Sukontawanich.

247
00:22:23,892 --> 00:22:26,574
You are a suspect of a homicide
and concealment of the body.

248
00:22:27,028 --> 00:22:28,748
Please go to the police station to testify.

249
00:22:29,614 --> 00:22:30,615
Follow me.

250
00:23:08,646 --> 00:23:09,647
Please get in.

251
00:23:18,764 --> 00:23:19,974
I'm proud of you

252
00:23:21,174 --> 00:23:22,654
for doing the right thing.

253
00:23:44,422 --> 00:23:45,423
I'm sorry

254
00:23:48,102 --> 00:23:50,094
for what my uncle and dad did

255
00:23:51,406 --> 00:23:52,654
to your parents.

256
00:23:57,241 --> 00:23:58,614
I'm sorry for everything

257
00:24:00,708 --> 00:24:01,868
that I have ever done to you.

258
00:24:06,078 --> 00:24:07,694
I know that you won't forgive me.

259
00:24:12,814 --> 00:24:14,254
Please go back to Mudan.

260
00:24:17,236 --> 00:24:18,614
This place is to cruel for you.

261
00:24:24,441 --> 00:24:25,542
I'm not the guy for you.

262
00:24:28,836 --> 00:24:29,837
And I…

263
00:24:32,934 --> 00:24:34,174
I don't deserve you.

264
00:24:38,617 --> 00:24:39,618
I'm sorry.

265
00:25:25,814 --> 00:25:26,815
Scent.

266
00:25:54,636 --> 00:25:55,637
Thank you.

267
00:27:26,030 --> 00:27:27,031
Mata,

268
00:27:28,214 --> 00:27:29,814
what is going to happen next?

269
00:27:31,988 --> 00:27:33,214
It will depend

270
00:27:34,894 --> 00:27:36,574
on both of them after this.

271
00:28:29,820 --> 00:28:30,821
Dad,

272
00:28:34,860 --> 00:28:36,214
Uncle Wittaya was arrested.

273
00:28:41,057 --> 00:28:43,414
You don't have to worry.

274
00:28:44,886 --> 00:28:46,726
The police said that
you should recover first.

275
00:28:58,081 --> 00:28:59,082
Yeah?

276
00:29:02,481 --> 00:29:03,561
What are you trying to say?

277
00:29:09,166 --> 00:29:10,167
I…

278
00:29:12,934 --> 00:29:14,694
I'm sorry.

279
00:29:19,300 --> 00:29:20,301
Sorry.

280
00:29:25,833 --> 00:29:26,894
It's okay.

281
00:29:28,454 --> 00:29:29,934
I'll be here with you no matter what.

282
00:29:30,868 --> 00:29:31,869
I won't go anywhere.

283
00:29:33,238 --> 00:29:34,239
I will be here will you.

284
00:30:34,153 --> 00:30:35,334
Give me the flowers, Tawan.

285
00:31:30,798 --> 00:31:31,799
Mom.

286
00:31:32,681 --> 00:31:33,682
You should rest here

287
00:31:36,078 --> 00:31:38,079
so you can watch sunrise before anyone.

288
00:31:40,092 --> 00:31:41,654
Mudan people

289
00:31:42,361 --> 00:31:43,574
are just like flowers,

290
00:31:44,409 --> 00:31:46,334
daylight, and dew.

291
00:31:47,636 --> 00:31:49,254
We will embrace you.

292
00:31:50,129 --> 00:31:52,414
You can finally rest in peace, Bussaba.

293
00:32:09,486 --> 00:32:10,694
Is it still working?

294
00:32:11,959 --> 00:32:13,174
It won't work up here.

295
00:32:13,988 --> 00:32:15,974
Mekin said that there's no signal.

296
00:32:17,406 --> 00:32:18,694
It means that

297
00:32:19,929 --> 00:32:23,514
if the city people try to contact us,

298
00:32:23,708 --> 00:32:25,014
we won't know about it, right?

299
00:32:31,364 --> 00:32:33,465
Are you going to be fine?

300
00:32:42,978 --> 00:32:44,574
Mudan people are like flowers.

301
00:32:47,206 --> 00:32:48,846
Our place is right here in the mountains.

302
00:33:04,009 --> 00:33:05,914
I can't live anywhere else.

303
00:33:37,494 --> 00:33:38,495
You miss him?

304
00:33:40,886 --> 00:33:43,134
Nope. I was just scrolling through my album.

305
00:33:44,454 --> 00:33:45,574
Why don't you go to see him?

306
00:33:48,832 --> 00:33:50,254
You don't remember what they said?

307
00:33:50,804 --> 00:33:52,454
They don't want us to be involved.

308
00:33:54,548 --> 00:33:58,114
And they want their Mudan
tribe to remain a secret.

309
00:33:59,593 --> 00:34:02,494
More importantly, I don't miss him at all.

310
00:34:09,414 --> 00:34:11,415
- Really?
- Yes.

311
00:34:13,774 --> 00:34:16,374
I think that he's cute

312
00:34:16,892 --> 00:34:18,214
and I wanted to pick on Scent.

313
00:34:19,788 --> 00:34:21,214
You don't have to pick on him.

314
00:34:22,511 --> 00:34:24,174
He has always been working in the lab.

315
00:34:26,830 --> 00:34:28,114
So pathetic.

316
00:34:40,438 --> 00:34:42,219
I want it to feel like

317
00:34:42,502 --> 00:34:44,774
standing amidst a
wildflower field in the north,

318
00:34:47,369 --> 00:34:48,573
and flowers are blooming.

319
00:34:51,894 --> 00:34:52,974
The base should be

320
00:34:55,053 --> 00:34:56,054
pine leaves,

321
00:34:57,690 --> 00:34:59,453
and the flowers should be

322
00:35:01,270 --> 00:35:04,014
roses and cape jasmine.

323
00:35:08,842 --> 00:35:09,843
Let's try.

324
00:35:40,134 --> 00:35:41,656
It's done, why don't you test it?

325
00:35:59,193 --> 00:36:01,174
How is it, Scent?

326
00:36:02,980 --> 00:36:05,854
Sun, I want it to have a smell of the sea.

327
00:36:06,974 --> 00:36:07,975
The sea?

328
00:36:08,575 --> 00:36:10,014
Yeah, warm like the sea.

329
00:36:12,083 --> 00:36:13,084
Okay.

330
00:36:35,414 --> 00:36:36,734
What do you think?

331
00:36:37,491 --> 00:36:38,492
Okay,

332
00:36:40,857 --> 00:36:43,214
but can I ask you to add one more?

333
00:36:43,654 --> 00:36:45,134
- What is it?
- I want it to be like…

334
00:36:46,054 --> 00:36:48,014
a park in the city.

335
00:36:48,294 --> 00:36:50,414
But we will mix three themes in one bottle.

336
00:36:50,494 --> 00:36:52,654
The scents won't blend together,
there are too many different layers.

337
00:36:52,814 --> 00:36:54,514
Come on, just try it.

338
00:36:55,664 --> 00:36:56,694
Fine, fine.

339
00:36:56,788 --> 00:36:58,614
The park?

340
00:36:59,913 --> 00:37:01,774
It should be grass with moss,

341
00:37:02,774 --> 00:37:06,174
mixing with plumeria.

342
00:37:06,446 --> 00:37:08,254
Let's do it.

343
00:37:25,054 --> 00:37:26,174
How is it?

344
00:37:29,694 --> 00:37:32,054
I think it is still missing something.

345
00:37:33,241 --> 00:37:34,242
What type of scent?

346
00:37:36,342 --> 00:37:37,343
Good question.

347
00:38:01,659 --> 00:38:02,734
Peony.

348
00:38:06,431 --> 00:38:07,432
Peony?

349
00:38:08,814 --> 00:38:10,294
What does 'Mudan' mean?

350
00:38:11,284 --> 00:38:13,374
It means peony.

351
00:38:15,834 --> 00:38:17,614
It symbolizes prosperity,

352
00:38:17,857 --> 00:38:18,859
honor,

353
00:38:20,174 --> 00:38:21,175
and…

354
00:38:22,337 --> 00:38:23,654
innocent love.

355
00:38:28,225 --> 00:38:29,226
Mudan.

356
00:38:49,598 --> 00:38:50,599
How many drops?

357
00:38:53,844 --> 00:38:54,845
One drop.

358
00:39:43,358 --> 00:39:45,734
I'm with Mr. Scent

359
00:39:45,803 --> 00:39:48,814
and the most hyped perfume at this moment.

360
00:39:49,414 --> 00:39:52,654
I'm talking about the 'Gaysorn'
perfume from Kusuma.

361
00:39:54,102 --> 00:39:56,814
Thank you everyone for
your support of our perfume.

362
00:39:57,169 --> 00:39:59,654
I took a sniff and I must tell you that

363
00:39:59,702 --> 00:40:01,134
this perfume is quite something.

364
00:40:01,494 --> 00:40:03,334
It contains different layers

365
00:40:03,729 --> 00:40:05,964
and I needed to ask Mr. Scent

366
00:40:06,172 --> 00:40:08,254
about the inspirations behind

367
00:40:08,332 --> 00:40:10,694
the creation of this perfume.

368
00:40:16,715 --> 00:40:17,854
The perfume

369
00:40:19,549 --> 00:40:22,174
is an extract of your preserved memoies.

370
00:40:23,577 --> 00:40:26,054
I named it 'Gaysorn'

371
00:40:27,171 --> 00:40:29,734
because I believe that scent

372
00:40:31,014 --> 00:40:32,334
is a form of contact.

373
00:40:34,910 --> 00:40:37,254
It's more than a touch of your skin

374
00:40:39,268 --> 00:40:41,974
but it's a touch of memories

375
00:40:43,662 --> 00:40:45,114
that are stored deep
down in your heart.

376
00:40:47,476 --> 00:40:49,654
It will remind you of good

377
00:40:51,454 --> 00:40:52,934
and unforgettable memories.

378
00:40:54,579 --> 00:40:56,580
Also, it will remind you of love.

379
00:40:59,284 --> 00:41:00,804
No matter where you are in this world,

380
00:41:03,081 --> 00:41:04,654
love will remain in your heart

381
00:41:07,545 --> 00:41:08,734
and it will never fade away.

382
00:41:33,731 --> 00:41:36,054
- Fire! Fire!
- Hey!

383
00:41:36,190 --> 00:41:38,694
Gaysorn! What happened? Move!

384
00:41:39,881 --> 00:41:42,294
Who told you to put foil in the microwave?

385
00:41:42,793 --> 00:41:43,794
You did.

386
00:41:44,548 --> 00:41:47,214
You told me to just put it in.

387
00:42:05,716 --> 00:42:06,717
What?

388
00:42:07,353 --> 00:42:08,374
It burned!

389
00:42:10,900 --> 00:42:11,974
Do you think I can eat it?

390
00:42:45,161 --> 00:42:46,654
Which one looks yummier?

391
00:42:50,494 --> 00:42:51,495
I think…

392
00:42:52,798 --> 00:42:53,799
This one.

393
00:42:55,654 --> 00:42:56,734
Can I have a bite?

394
00:42:59,662 --> 00:43:00,663
Sure.

395
00:44:28,665 --> 00:44:30,654
In this capital increase agreement,

396
00:44:30,878 --> 00:44:33,014
Mekin will hold more shares,

397
00:44:33,116 --> 00:44:34,945
up to 15% of Kusuma.

398
00:44:35,142 --> 00:44:38,177
It is valued at 120 million baht.

399
00:44:38,710 --> 00:44:39,734
The conditions

400
00:44:40,012 --> 00:44:43,174
will follow the same agreement
as what's been drafted.

401
00:44:43,482 --> 00:44:45,214
If you all are ready,

402
00:44:45,347 --> 00:44:46,914
please sign on both copies.

403
00:45:14,852 --> 00:45:16,774
What's wrong with your
hand? What did you do?

404
00:45:22,406 --> 00:45:23,407
It's nothing.

405
00:45:46,177 --> 00:45:49,894
Happy Birthday to You.

406
00:45:54,457 --> 00:45:55,574
Happy Birthday!

407
00:45:57,774 --> 00:45:58,775
Make a wish.

408
00:46:12,321 --> 00:46:13,714
I wish…

409
00:46:18,918 --> 00:46:20,334
we'll become a real couple. Can we?

410
00:46:25,654 --> 00:46:26,654
Sure.

411
00:47:31,382 --> 00:47:32,414
Hello, Julie.

412
00:47:33,114 --> 00:47:34,115
I see.

413
00:47:34,609 --> 00:47:36,694
You can send it to me now.

414
00:47:47,652 --> 00:47:49,774
We can't make any mistakes
with our partners in Europe.

415
00:47:50,774 --> 00:47:53,214
If you finish with the revised version,
you can send it to me.

416
00:47:54,516 --> 00:47:56,294
I'll send you the reference for checking.

417
00:48:36,350 --> 00:48:38,116
Scent? Are you okay?

418
00:48:39,214 --> 00:48:40,334
You look so pale.

419
00:48:42,264 --> 00:48:43,265
I'm fine.

420
00:48:43,748 --> 00:48:44,749
Just a little dizzy.

421
00:48:45,428 --> 00:48:46,429
I need to use a bathroom.

422
00:48:47,254 --> 00:48:48,255
Are you okay?

423
00:48:51,502 --> 00:48:53,494
Scent! Hey!

424
00:48:54,022 --> 00:48:55,788
Scent! Scent!

425
00:48:56,434 --> 00:48:57,435
Scent!

426
00:48:57,585 --> 00:48:59,614
Who's here? Scent!

427
00:49:10,454 --> 00:49:12,315
Gaysorn! Gaysorn!

428
00:49:13,446 --> 00:49:14,447
Gaysorn!

429
00:49:14,894 --> 00:49:16,734
- Gaysorn!
- Tawan?

430
00:49:17,425 --> 00:49:18,426
What's the matter?

431
00:49:18,737 --> 00:49:20,694
I went to the market earlier

432
00:49:21,030 --> 00:49:22,101
and I saw Mekin.

433
00:49:23,910 --> 00:49:24,934
He wanted to see you.

434
00:49:26,251 --> 00:49:28,771
He said that he will wait for you
at the national park's office.

435
00:49:42,956 --> 00:49:44,054
It's noon already.

436
00:49:45,073 --> 00:49:46,774
Are you sure that Gaysorn will be here?

437
00:49:56,694 --> 00:49:57,695
See?

438
00:50:03,755 --> 00:50:05,454
We were just wondering if you'd show up.

439
00:50:11,454 --> 00:50:12,455
Hey,

440
00:50:14,681 --> 00:50:15,864
he's not coming.

441
00:50:25,404 --> 00:50:26,714
He wanted you to have this.

442
00:50:30,774 --> 00:50:33,334
This is a perfume that Scent developed

443
00:50:34,177 --> 00:50:35,178
because he misses you.

444
00:50:47,737 --> 00:50:48,974
He misses you a lot.

445
00:51:53,073 --> 00:51:54,614
I want it to feel like

446
00:51:55,054 --> 00:51:57,254
standing amidst a
wildflower field in the north.

447
00:52:17,126 --> 00:52:20,214
A scent to remind you of park in the city.

448
00:52:24,934 --> 00:52:26,114
A scent of the sea,

449
00:52:27,254 --> 00:52:28,714
the warmth of the sea.

450
00:52:47,782 --> 00:52:49,974
Mudan means peony.

451
00:52:50,734 --> 00:52:52,574
It symbolizes prosperity,

452
00:52:54,014 --> 00:52:55,015
honor,

453
00:52:56,214 --> 00:52:57,215
and…

454
00:52:58,268 --> 00:52:59,734
innocent love.

455
00:53:55,204 --> 00:53:56,205
I think…

456
00:53:57,331 --> 00:53:59,054
Scent isn't the only one who loves Gaysorn.

457
00:54:02,001 --> 00:54:03,914
Gaysorn loves Scent so much as well.

458
00:54:06,390 --> 00:54:07,694
Why isn't he here?

459
00:54:12,854 --> 00:54:14,164
It's not like he didn't want to come,

460
00:54:16,155 --> 00:54:17,374
but he couldn't be here.

461
00:54:24,748 --> 00:54:25,774
What's wrong with him?

462
00:54:26,769 --> 00:54:29,614
Where is Scent?

463
00:58:54,974 --> 00:58:56,094
I'm not dreaming, am I?

464
00:59:15,387 --> 00:59:16,507
Is this real enough for you?

465
00:59:26,710 --> 00:59:28,134
I never thought you'd be back.

466
00:59:32,212 --> 00:59:33,494
Your perfume

467
00:59:34,212 --> 00:59:35,514
told me to come back to you.

468
00:59:50,395 --> 00:59:53,214
It really is you. It's you.

469
00:59:55,548 --> 00:59:56,814
I missed you.

470
01:00:49,004 --> 01:00:52,014
I bought this plot of land
because it is close to the mountains.

471
01:00:55,291 --> 01:00:56,974
When I missed you,

472
01:00:57,585 --> 01:00:58,974
I would plant flowers here.

473
01:01:00,001 --> 01:01:01,002
You did?

474
01:01:01,564 --> 01:01:02,565
That's right.

475
01:01:03,894 --> 01:01:05,574
And I will keep on planting them.

476
01:01:07,523 --> 01:01:09,414
Because I will miss you forever.

477
01:01:15,198 --> 01:01:16,199
Hey!

478
01:01:16,947 --> 01:01:17,948
What?

479
01:01:20,329 --> 01:01:22,049
I don't think you need to plant any flowers.

480
01:01:23,326 --> 01:01:24,327
Why's that?

481
01:01:26,134 --> 01:01:27,494
When we stay together,

482
01:01:29,587 --> 01:01:31,094
why would you miss me?

483
01:01:36,380 --> 01:01:37,381
Really?

484
01:01:47,523 --> 01:01:48,524
Gaysorn,

485
01:01:50,985 --> 01:01:51,986
I love you.

486
01:01:58,116 --> 01:01:59,117
And I…

487
01:02:01,652 --> 01:02:02,734
You don't have to ell me.

488
01:02:04,425 --> 01:02:06,514
You scent tells it all.

489
01:02:09,838 --> 01:02:11,334
You love me too, don't you?

490
01:03:38,814 --> 01:03:40,734
[The end.]
